    "recap_headline": "Boston College Athletics",
    "recap_text": "CHESTNUT HILL, Mass. \u2014\nBoston College Baseball (13-8, 3-3 ACC) defeated UMass Lowell (7-9), 12-2 on Wednesday afternoon.\nChase Hartsell\nearned his first career start for the Eagles and threw three innings, allowing three hits and just one earned run. He was replaced by\nEthan Marzo\n, who made his Boston College debut and threw a scoreless inning, allowing just one hit. He was replaced by\nJacob Burnham\n, who threw three innings of one-run ball while striking out two.\nPeter Schaefer\nfinished the game by throwing an inning and allowing just one hit.\nThe Eagles struck first after getting runners on first and third courtesy of a\nNick Wang\ntriple and a walk from\nJack Toomey\n; they were then both brought in on\nDanny Surowiec's\nfirst career home run, which made it 3-0 Eagles.\nIn the top of the second, the River Hawks made it 3-1 after an RBI double brought in a runner from second.\nThe Eagles would tack on two more in the bottom half of the second when\nTy Mainolfi\ndoubled in\nJulio Solier\nfrom second. Mainolfi then stole third and was driven in on a single from Wang to make it 5-1 Boston College.\nIn the bottom of the fourth, the Eagles made it 7-1 when\nJack Toomey\nlined a single to right to score\nColin Larson\nand\nJulio Solier\n.\nLarson added his second home run of the season in the bottom of the fifth that brought in\nJace Roossien\nfrom second and made it 9-1 in favor of Boston College.\nToomey hit the Eagles' third home run of the day in the bottom of the sixth that scored Wang as well to make it 11-1 Boston College.\nUMass Lowell made it 11-2 in the top of the seventh inning on a single to right field that scored a runner from second base.\nIn the bottom of the eighth, the Eagles put runners on second and third following a sacrifice bunt by\nBen Williams\n.\nEsteban Garcia\nthen lined a single to center field, which brought in the winning run from third.\nUp Next:\nThe Eagles will return to action on Friday at 3:00 p.m. when they take on California in a return to ACC play."
